---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const jsonLd = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "name": "Terms & Conditions",
    "url": "https://theeduassist.com/terms-and-conditions/",
    "description": "Read the terms for using TheEduAssist’s website, submitting project inquiries, viewing service information, and engaging with our e-learning design services."
  }
];
---
<Layout
  title="Terms & Conditions | TheEduAssist"
  description="Read the terms for using TheEduAssist’s website, submitting project inquiries, viewing service information, and engaging with our e-learning design services."
  canonicalPath="/terms-and-conditions/"
  type="website"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>

  <section class="py-20 bg-slate-100 px-4 text-center">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4 max-w-4xl mx-auto">Terms & Conditions</h1>
    <p class="text-slate-600">Last updated: 2026</p>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 prose prose-slate">

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">1. Introduction</h2>
      <p>These Terms govern use of TheEduAssist website and website content.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">2. Website information</h2>
      <p>The website provides information about e-learning design, course creation, Kajabi services, LMS migration, content conversion, AI-powered e-learning support, funnels, automation, support services, blog resources, and case studies.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">3. No automatic client relationship</h2>
      <p>Submitting a form, email, or chatting with us via the live chat widget does not automatically create a client relationship. A project begins only after scope, timeline, pricing, payment terms, and agreement are confirmed.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">4. Starting prices and Payment</h2>
      <p>Starting prices shown on the website are estimates and not fixed final quotes. Final scope depends on content volume, platform, course length, page count, review rounds, automations, integrations, timeline, and launch support. Payment instructions or an invoice are shared only after the final scope is confirmed.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">5. Project inquiries</h2>
      <p>Submitting a 24–48 Hour Review request does not guarantee acceptance of a project. TheEduAssist may accept, decline, or recommend a different service path.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">6. Payment and project terms</h2>
      <p>Specific payment terms, milestones, revision rounds, deliverables, and timelines will be agreed separately before project work begins.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">7. Client responsibilities</h2>
      <p>Clients are responsible for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>providing accurate project information</li>
        <li>having rights to the content they provide</li>
        <li>reviewing deliverables in a timely manner</li>
        <li>approving content before launch</li>
        <li>providing platform access only through secure approved methods</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">8. Content ownership</h2>
      <p>Client-provided materials remain the client’s responsibility and ownership.</p>
      <p>Final ownership and usage rights of deliverables depend on the agreed project terms.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">9. AI-assisted work</h2>
      <p>TheEduAssist may use AI-assisted workflows to support planning, drafting, organizing, summarizing, or improving learning content, but human review and project judgment remain part of the process.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">10. Website AI/share tools</h2>
      <p>The website may provide AI prompt-copy and share tools for visitor convenience. TheEduAssist is not responsible for outputs generated by third-party AI tools or content users choose to paste into those platforms.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">11. Case studies</h2>
      <p>Case studies show real project types and outcomes based on approved public-facing information. Some client names or internal details may be omitted for confidentiality.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">12. No guaranteed results</h2>
      <p>TheEduAssist does not guarantee specific revenue, enrollment numbers, completion rates, rankings, platform performance, or business results unless stated in a signed agreement.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">13. Third-party platforms</h2>
      <p>Kajabi, LMS platforms, Google Forms, Google Sheets, Sanity, Firebase, analytics tools, AI assistants, social networks, and other third-party services have their own terms and policies.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">14. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>Website content, design, copy, visuals, and brand materials belong to TheEduAssist unless otherwise stated.</p>
      <p>Users may not copy or reuse website content without permission.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">15. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>TheEduAssist is not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential losses from using the website or third-party tools.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">16. Changes to terms</h2>
      <p>TheEduAssist may update these Terms.</p>

      <h2 class="text-brand-navy">17. Contact</h2>
      <p>Email: <a href="mailto:Info@theeduassist.com" class="text-brand-primary hover:underline">Info@theeduassist.com</a></p>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
